Metadata: Alongshore transport of large woody debris on the Elwha River Delta
Poster presented at the 2014 Salish Sea Conference, Seattle, Washington, April 30-May 2, 2014

In the Elwha River watershed, large woody debris (LWD) is being tracked in association with the removal of the Glines Canyon and Elwha Dams. In 2011, before sediment from the dam removal arrived on the beach, 27 logs were tagged on the Elwha River delta east of the river mouth along
